revisions.description: pre-RFC draft v6: Modified by David Raftus to update references, boilerplate to format suggested by IPCDN workgroup. Also clarified descriptions of some objects, added size constraints to selected objects to fix compiler warnings. pre-RFC draft v5: Modified by David Raftus to add channel utilization related objects, upstream channel equalization related objects, a cmts upstream minislot counter table, a cmts downstream byte counter table, 64 bit versions of existing 32 bit docsIfSigQTable objects, and perform some editorial adjustments. pre-RFC draft v4: Modified by David Raftus to fix docsIfUpChannelWidth range in compliance statements to accommodate 6.4Mhz channel at 5.12 Msymbol/sec. Also adjusted description of docsIfUpChannelStatus to use correct rowStatus terminology. pre-RFC draft v3: Modified by David Raftus to add new textual convention describing upstream modulation status. Also clarified some object descriptions, fixed error in docsIfSignalQualityEntry, fixed upstreamTable compliance statements. pre-RFC draft v2: Modified by David Raftus to add capability to adjust and verify upstream channel parameters as a group. Also adjusted syntax and clarified descriptions of selected objects. pre-RFC draft v1: Modified by Aviv Goren and David Raftus to accommodate Docsis 2.0 Advanced Phy capabilities, as well as to incorporate objects from the docsIfExt mib. Modified by Rich Woundy to use IPv6-friendly address objects, to accommodate EuroDOCSIS, and to correct the SYNTAX of various objects.

Initial Version, published as RFC 2670. Modified by Mike StJohns to fix problems identified by the first pass of the MIB doctor. Of special note, docsIfRangingResp and docsIfCmtsInsertionInterval were obsoleted and replaced by other objects with the same functionality, but more appropriate SYNTAX.

docsIfMib.description: This is the MIB Module for DOCSIS 2.0 compliant Radio Frequency (RF) interfaces in Cable Modems (CM) and Cable Modem Termination Systems (CMTS).

TenthdBmV.name: TenthdBmV
TenthdBmV.description: This data type represents power levels that are normally expressed in dBmV. Units are in tenths of a dBmV; for example, 5.1 dBmV will be represented as 51.

TenthdB.name: TenthdB
TenthdB.description: This data type represents power levels that are normally expressed in dB. Units are in tenths of a dB; for example, 5.1 dB will be represented as 51.

DocsisQosVersion.name: DocsisQosVersion
DocsisQosVersion.description: Indicates the quality of service level.

DocsisUpstreamType.name: DocsisUpstreamType
DocsisUpstreamType.description: Indicates the DOCSIS Upstream Channel Type.

DocsisUpstreamTypeStatus.name: DocsisUpstreamTypeStatus
DocsisUpstreamTypeStatus.description: Indicates the DOCSIS Upstream Channel Type Status. The shared channel indicator type is not valid, since this type is used to specifically identify PHY mode.

docsIfDownstreamChannelTable.name: docsIfDownstreamChannelTable
docsIfDownstreamChannelTable.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 6-12 and Table 6-13.
docsIfDownstreamChannelTable.description: This table describes the attributes of downstream channels (frequency bands).

docsIfDownstreamChannelEntry.name: docsIfDownstreamChannelEntry
docsIfDownstreamChannelEntry.description: An entry provides a list of attributes for a single Downstream channel. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableDownstream(128).

docsIfDownChannelId.name: docsIfDownChannelId
docsIfDownChannelId.description: The Cable Modem Termination System (CMTS) identification of the downstream channel within this particular MAC interface. If the interface is down, the object returns the most current value. If the downstream channel ID is unknown, this object returns a value of 0.

docsIfDownChannelFrequency.name: docsIfDownChannelFrequency
docsIfDownChannelFrequency.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Tables 4-1, 6-14.
docsIfDownChannelFrequency.description: The center of the downstream frequency associated with this channel. This object will return the current tuner frequency. If a CMTS provides IF output, this object will return 0, unless this CMTS is in control of the final downstream RF frequency. See the associated compliance object for a description of valid frequencies that may be written to this object.

docsIfDownChannelWidth.name: docsIfDownChannelWidth
docsIfDownChannelWidth.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 6-14.
docsIfDownChannelWidth.description: The bandwidth of this downstream channel. Most implementations are expected to support a channel width of 6 MHz (North America) and/or 8 MHz (Europe). See the associated compliance object for a description of the valid channel widths for this object.

docsIfDownChannelModulation.name: docsIfDownChannelModulation
docsIfDownChannelModulation.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 6-14.
docsIfDownChannelModulation.description: The modulation type associated with this downstream channel. If the interface is down, this object either returns the configured value (CMTS), the most current value (CM), or the value of unknown(1). See the associated conformance object for write conditions and limitations. See the reference for specifics on the modulation profiles implied by qam64 and qam256.

docsIfDownChannelInterleave.name: docsIfDownChannelInterleave
docsIfDownChannelInterleave.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 6-13.
docsIfDownChannelInterleave.description: The Forward Error Correction (FEC) interleaving used for this downstream channel. Values are defined as follows: taps8Increment16(3): protection 5.9/4.1 usec, latency .22/.15 msec taps16Increment8(4): protection 12/8.2 usec, latency .48/.33 msec taps32Increment4(5): protection 24/16 usec, latency .98/.68 msec taps64Increment2(6): protection 47/33 usec, latency 2/1.4 msec taps128Increment1(7): protection 95/66 usec, latency 4/2.8 msec taps12increment17(8): protection 18/14 usec, latency 0.43/0.32 msec taps12increment17 is implemented in conformance with EuroDOCSIS document 'Adapted MIB-definitions - and a clarification for MPEG-related issues - for EuroDOCSIS cable modem systems' by tComLabs and should only be used for a EuroDOCSIS MAC interface. If the interface is down, this object either returns the configured value (CMTS), the most current value (CM), or the value of unknown(1). The value of other(2) is returned if the interleave is known but not defined in the above list. See the associated conformance object for write conditions and limitations. See the reference for the FEC configuration described by the setting of this object.

docsIfDownChannelPower.name: docsIfDownChannelPower
docsIfDownChannelPower.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 6-15.
docsIfDownChannelPower.description: At the CMTS, the operational transmit power. At the CM, the received power level. If the interface is down, this object either returns the configured value (CMTS), the most current value (CM) or the value of 0. See the associated conformance object for write conditions and limitations. See the reference for recommended and required power levels.

docsIfDownChannelAnnex.name: docsIfDownChannelAnnex
docsIfDownChannelAnnex.reference: Document Adapted MIB-definitions and a clarification for MPEG-related issues for EuroDOCSIS cable modem systems v1.01, tComLabs, May 2000, Section 2.2
docsIfDownChannelAnnex.description: The value of this object indicates the conformance of the implementation to important regional cable standards. annexA : Annex A from ITU-J83 is used. annexB : Annex B from ITU-J83 is used. annexC : Annex C from ITU-J83 is used. AnnexB is used for DOCSIS implementations

docsIfUpstreamChannelTable.name: docsIfUpstreamChannelTable
docsIfUpstreamChannelTable.description: This table describes the attributes of attached upstream channels.

docsIfUpstreamChannelEntry.name: docsIfUpstreamChannelEntry
docsIfUpstreamChannelEntry.description: List of attributes for a single upstream channel. For Docsis 2.0 CMTSs, an entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableUpstreamChannel (205). For Docsis 1.x CM/CMTSs and Docsis 2.0 CMs, an entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableUpstreamInterface (129).

docsIfUpChannelId.name: docsIfUpChannelId
docsIfUpChannelId.description: The CMTS identification of the upstream channel.

docsIfUpChannelFrequency.name: docsIfUpChannelFrequency
docsIfUpChannelFrequency.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 4-2.
docsIfUpChannelFrequency.description: The center of the frequency band associated with this upstream interface. This object returns 0 if the frequency is undefined or unknown. Minimum permitted upstream frequency is 5,000,000 Hz for current technology. See the associated conformance object for write conditions and limitations.

docsIfUpChannelWidth.name: docsIfUpChannelWidth
docsIfUpChannelWidth.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 6-12.
docsIfUpChannelWidth.description: The bandwidth of this upstream interface. This object returns 0 if the interface width is undefined or unknown. Minimum permitted interface width is 200,000 Hz currently. See the associated conformance object for write conditions and limitations.

docsIfUpChannelModulationProfile.name: docsIfUpChannelModulationProfile
docsIfUpChannelModulationProfile.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfUpChannelModulationProfile.description: An entry identical to the docsIfModIndex in the docsIfCmtsModulationTable that describes this channel. This channel is further instantiated there by a grouping of interval usage codes which together fully describe the channel modulation. This object returns 0 if the docsIfCmtsModulationTable entry does not exist or docsIfCmtsModulationTable is empty. See the associated conformance object for write conditions and limitations.

docsIfUpChannelSlotSize.name: docsIfUpChannelSlotSize
docsIfUpChannelSlotSize.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.1.2.4.
docsIfUpChannelSlotSize.description: Applicable to TDMA and ATDMA channel types only. The number of 6.25 microsecond ticks in each upstream mini-slot. Returns zero if the value is undefined, unknown or in case of an SCDMA channel. See the associated conformance object for write conditions and limitations.

docsIfUpChannelTxTimingOffset.name: docsIfUpChannelTxTimingOffset
docsIfUpChannelTxTimingOffset.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.18.
docsIfUpChannelTxTimingOffset.description: At the CM, a measure of the current round trip time obtained from the ranging offset (initial ranging offset + ranging offset adjustments). At the CMTS, the maximum of timing offset, among all the CMs that are/were present on the channel, taking into account all ( initial + periodic ) timing offset corrections that were sent for each of the CMs. Generally, these measurements are positive, but if the measurements are negative, the value of this object is zero. Used for timing of CM upstream transmissions to ensure synchronized arrivals at the CMTS. Units are in terms of (6.25 microseconds/64).

docsIfUpChannelRangingBackoffStart.name: docsIfUpChannelRangingBackoffStart
docsIfUpChannelRangingBackoffStart.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.3.4.
docsIfUpChannelRangingBackoffStart.description: The initial random backoff window to use when retrying Ranging Requests. Expressed as a power of 2. A value of 16 at the CMTS indicates that a proprietary adaptive retry mechanism is to be used. See the associated conformance object for write conditions and limitations.

docsIfUpChannelRangingBackoffEnd.name: docsIfUpChannelRangingBackoffEnd
docsIfUpChannelRangingBackoffEnd.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.3.4.
docsIfUpChannelRangingBackoffEnd.description: The final random backoff window to use when retrying Ranging Requests. Expressed as a power of 2. A value of 16 at the CMTS indicates that a proprietary adaptive retry mechanism is to be used. See the associated conformance object for write conditions and limitations.

docsIfUpChannelTxBackoffStart.name: docsIfUpChannelTxBackoffStart
docsIfUpChannelTxBackoffStart.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.3.4.
docsIfUpChannelTxBackoffStart.description: The initial random backoff window to use when retrying transmissions. Expressed as a power of 2. A value of 16 at the CMTS indicates that a proprietary adaptive retry mechanism is to be used. See the associated conformance object for write conditions and limitations.

docsIfUpChannelTxBackoffEnd.name: docsIfUpChannelTxBackoffEnd
docsIfUpChannelTxBackoffEnd.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.3.4.
docsIfUpChannelTxBackoffEnd.description: The final random backoff window to use when retrying transmissions. Expressed as a power of 2. A value of 16 at the CMTS indicates that a proprietary adaptive retry mechanism is to be used. See the associated conformance object for write conditions and limitations.

docsIfUpChannelScdmaActiveCodes.name: docsIfUpChannelScdmaActiveCodes
docsIfUpChannelScdmaActiveCodes.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.11.2.1.
docsIfUpChannelScdmaActiveCodes.description: Applicable for SCDMA channel types only. Number of active codes. Returns zero for Non-SCDMA channel types. Note that legal values from 64..128 MUST be non-prime.

docsIfUpChannelScdmaCodesPerSlot.name: docsIfUpChannelScdmaCodesPerSlot
docsIfUpChannelScdmaCodesPerSlot.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.11.2.1.
docsIfUpChannelScdmaCodesPerSlot.description: Applicable for SCDMA channel types only. The number of SCDMA codes per mini-slot. Returns zero if the value is undefined, unknown or in case of a TDMA or ATDMA channel.

docsIfUpChannelScdmaFrameSize.name: docsIfUpChannelScdmaFrameSize
docsIfUpChannelScdmaFrameSize.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.12.
docsIfUpChannelScdmaFrameSize.description: Applicable for SCDMA channel types only. SCDMA Frame size in units of spreading intervals. This value returns zero for non SCDMA Profiles.

docsIfUpChannelScdmaHoppingSeed.name: docsIfUpChannelScdmaHoppingSeed
docsIfUpChannelScdmaHoppingSeed.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.14.1.
docsIfUpChannelScdmaHoppingSeed.description: Applicable for SCDMA channel types only. 15 bit seed used for code hopping sequence initialization. Returns zero for non-SCDMA channel types.

docsIfUpChannelType.name: docsIfUpChannelType
docsIfUpChannelType.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.1.
docsIfUpChannelType.description: Defines the Upstream channel type. Given the channel type, other channel attributes can be checked for value validity at the time of entry creation and update.

docsIfUpChannelCloneFrom.name: docsIfUpChannelCloneFrom
docsIfUpChannelCloneFrom.description: Intended for use when a temporary inactive upstream table row is created for the purpose of manipulating SCDMA parameters for an active row. Refer to the descriptions of docsIfUpChannelStatus and docsIfUpChannelUpdate for details of this procedure. This object contains the ifIndex value of the active upstream row whose SCDMA parameters are to be adjusted. Although this object was created to facilitate SCDMA parameter adjustment, it may also be used at the vendor's discretion for non-SCDMA parameter adjustment. This object must contain a value of zero for active upstream rows.

docsIfUpChannelUpdate.name: docsIfUpChannelUpdate
docsIfUpChannelUpdate.description: Used to perform the transfer of adjusted SCDMA parameters from the temporary upstream row to the active upstream row indicated by the docsIfUpChannelCloneFrom object. The transfer is initiated through an SNMP SET of TRUE to this object. The SNMP SET will fail with a GEN_ERROR (snmpv1) or COMMIT_FAILED_ERROR (snmpv2c/v3) if the adjusted SCDMA parameter values are not compatible with each other. Although this object was created to facilitate SCDMA parameter adjustment, it may also be used at the vendor's discretion for non-SCDMA parameter adjustment. An SNMP GET of this object always returns FALSE.

docsIfUpChannelStatus.name: docsIfUpChannelStatus
docsIfUpChannelStatus.description: This object is generally intended to be used for the creation of a temporary inactive upstream row for the purpose of adjusting the SCDMA channel parameters of an active upstream row. The recommended procedure is: 1) Create an inactive row through an SNMP SET using createAndWait(5). Use an ifIndex value outside the operational range of the system. 2) Set the docsIfUpChannelCloneFrom field to the ifIndex value of the active row whose SCDMA parameters require adjustment. 3) Adjust the SCDMA parameter values using the new temporary inactive row. 4) Update the active row by setting object docsIfUpChannelUpdate to TRUE. This SET will fail if the adjusted SCDMA parameters are not compatible with each other. 5) Delete the temporary row through an SNMP SET using DELETE. The following restrictions apply to this object: 1) This object must contain a value of active(1) for active rows. 2) Temporary inactive rows must be created using createAndWait(5). 3) The only possible status change of a row created using createAndWait(5) (ie notInService(2)) is to destroy(6). These temporary rows must never become active. 4) A status transition from active (1) to destroy (6) is not permitted. Entries with docsIfUpChannelStatus set to active(1) are logically linked to a physical interface, not temporarily created to clone parameters. The Interface MIB [RFC2863] ifAdminStatus should be used to take an Upstream Channel offline. Although this object was created to facilitate SCDMA parameter adjustment, it may also be used at the vendor's discretion for non-SCDMA parameter adjustment.

docsIfUpChannelPreEqEnable.name: docsIfUpChannelPreEqEnable
docsIfUpChannelPreEqEnable.description: At the CMTS, used to enable or disable pre-equalization on the upstream channel represented by this table instance. At the CM, this object is read-only and reflects the status of pre-equalization as represented in the RNG-RSP.

docsIfQosProfileTable.name: docsIfQosProfileTable
docsIfQosProfileTable.description: Describes the attributes for each class of service.

docsIfQosProfileEntry.name: docsIfQosProfileEntry
docsIfQosProfileEntry.description: Describes the attributes for a single class of service. If implemented as read-create in the Cable Modem Termination System, creation of entries in this table is controlled by the value of docsIfCmtsQosProfilePermissions. If implemented as read-only, entries are created based on information in REG-REQ MAC messages received from Cable Modems (Cable Modem Termination System implementation), or based on information extracted from the TFTP option file (Cable Modem implementation). In the Cable Modem Termination system, read-only entries are removed if no longer referenced by docsIfCmtsServiceTable. An entry in this table must not be removed while it is referenced by an entry in docsIfCmServiceTable (Cable Modem) or docsIfCmtsServiceTable (Cable Modem Termination System). An entry in this table should not be changeable while it is referenced by an entry in docsIfCmtsServiceTable. If this table is created automatically, there should only be a single entry for each Class of Service. Multiple entries with the same Class of Service parameters are not recommended.

docsIfQosProfIndex.name: docsIfQosProfIndex
docsIfQosProfIndex.description: The index value that uniquely identifies an entry in the docsIfQosProfileTable.

docsIfQosProfPriority.name: docsIfQosProfPriority
docsIfQosProfPriority.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Appendix C.1.1.4.
docsIfQosProfPriority.description: A relative priority assigned to this service when allocating bandwidth. Zero indicates lowest priority and seven indicates highest priority. Interpretation of priority is device-specific. MUST NOT be changed while this row is active.

docsIfQosProfMaxUpBandwidth.name: docsIfQosProfMaxUpBandwidth
docsIfQosProfMaxUpBandwidth.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Appendix C.1.1.4.
docsIfQosProfMaxUpBandwidth.description: The maximum upstream bandwidth, in bits per second, allowed for a service with this service class. Zero if there is no restriction of upstream bandwidth. MUST NOT be changed while this row is active.

docsIfQosProfGuarUpBandwidth.name: docsIfQosProfGuarUpBandwidth
docsIfQosProfGuarUpBandwidth.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Appendix C.1.1.4.
docsIfQosProfGuarUpBandwidth.description: Minimum guaranteed upstream bandwidth, in bits per second, allowed for a service with this service class. MUST NOT be changed while this row is active.

docsIfQosProfMaxDownBandwidth.name: docsIfQosProfMaxDownBandwidth
docsIfQosProfMaxDownBandwidth.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Appendix C.1.1.4.
docsIfQosProfMaxDownBandwidth.description: The maximum downstream bandwidth, in bits per second, allowed for a service with this service class. Zero if there is no restriction of downstream bandwidth. MUST NOT be changed while this row is active.

docsIfQosProfMaxTxBurst.name: docsIfQosProfMaxTxBurst
docsIfQosProfMaxTxBurst.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, C.1.1.4.
docsIfQosProfMaxTxBurst.description: The maximum number of mini-slots that may be requested for a single upstream transmission. A value of zero means there is no limit. MUST NOT be changed while this row is active. This object has been deprecated and replaced by docsIfQosProfMaxTransmitBurst, to fix a mismatch of the units and value range with respect to the DOCSIS Maximum Upstream Channel Transmit Burst Configuration Setting.

docsIfQosProfBaselinePrivacy.name: docsIfQosProfBaselinePrivacy
docsIfQosProfBaselinePrivacy.description: Indicates whether Baseline Privacy is enabled for this service class. MUST NOT be changed while this row is active.

docsIfQosProfStatus.name: docsIfQosProfStatus
docsIfQosProfStatus.description: This is object is to used to create or delete rows in this table. This object MUST NOT be changed from active while the row is referenced by the any entry in either docsIfCmServiceTable (on the CM), or the docsIfCmtsServiceTable (on the CMTS).

docsIfQosProfMaxTransmitBurst.name: docsIfQosProfMaxTransmitBurst
docsIfQosProfMaxTransmitBurst.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Appendix C.1.1.4.
docsIfQosProfMaxTransmitBurst.description: The maximum number of bytes that may be requested for a single upstream transmission. A value of zero means there is no limit. Note: This value does not include any physical layer overhead. MUST NOT be changed while this row is active.

docsIfSignalQualityTable.name: docsIfSignalQualityTable
docsIfSignalQualityTable.description: At the CM, describes the PHY signal quality of downstream channels. At the CMTS, describes the PHY signal quality of upstream channels. At the CMTS, this table may exclude contention intervals.

docsIfSignalQualityEntry.name: docsIfSignalQualityEntry
docsIfSignalQualityEntry.description: At the CM, describes the PHY characteristics of a downstream channel. At the CMTS, describes the PHY signal quality of an upstream channel. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableDownstream(128) for Cable Modems. For Docsis 1.1 Cable Modem Termination Systems, an entry exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableUpstream (129). For Docsis 2.0 Cable Modem Termination Systems, an entry exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableUpstreamChannel (205).

docsIfSigQIncludesContention.name: docsIfSigQIncludesContention
docsIfSigQIncludesContention.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.4.1
docsIfSigQIncludesContention.description: true(1) if this CMTS includes contention intervals in the counters in this table. Always false(2) for CMs.

docsIfSigQUnerroreds.name: docsIfSigQUnerroreds
docsIfSigQUnerroreds.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.5.
docsIfSigQUnerroreds.description: Codewords received on this channel without error. This includes all codewords, whether or not they were part of frames destined for this device.

docsIfSigQCorrecteds.name: docsIfSigQCorrecteds
docsIfSigQCorrecteds.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.5.
docsIfSigQCorrecteds.description: Codewords received on this channel with correctable errors. This includes all codewords, whether or not they were part of frames destined for this device.

docsIfSigQUncorrectables.name: docsIfSigQUncorrectables
docsIfSigQUncorrectables.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.5.
docsIfSigQUncorrectables.description: Codewords received on this channel with uncorrectable errors. This includes all codewords, whether or not they were part of frames destined for this device.

docsIfSigQSignalNoise.name: docsIfSigQSignalNoise
docsIfSigQSignalNoise.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Tables 4-1 and 4-2
docsIfSigQSignalNoise.description: Signal/Noise ratio as perceived for this channel. At the CM, describes the Signal/Noise of the downstream channel. At the CMTS, describes the average Signal/Noise of the upstream channel.

docsIfSigQMicroreflections.name: docsIfSigQMicroreflections
docsIfSigQMicroreflections.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Tables 4-1 and 4-2
docsIfSigQMicroreflections.description: Total microreflections including in-channel response as perceived on this interface, measured in dBc below the signal level. This object is not assumed to return an absolutely accurate value, but should give a rough indication of microreflections received on this interface. It is up to the implementer to provide information as accurate as possible.

docsIfSigQEqualizationData.name: docsIfSigQEqualizationData
docsIfSigQEqualizationData.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.3.2.
docsIfSigQEqualizationData.description: At the CM, returns the equalization data for the downstream channel. At the CMTS, returns the average equalization data for the upstream channel. Returns an empty string if the value is unknown or if there is no equalization data available or defined.

docsIfSigQExtUnerroreds.name: docsIfSigQExtUnerroreds
docsIfSigQExtUnerroreds.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.5.
docsIfSigQExtUnerroreds.description: Codewords received on this channel without error. This includes all codewords, whether or not they were part of frames destined for this device. This is the 64 bit version of docsIfSigQUnerroreds.

docsIfSigQExtCorrecteds.name: docsIfSigQExtCorrecteds
docsIfSigQExtCorrecteds.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.5.
docsIfSigQExtCorrecteds.description: Codewords received on this channel with correctable errors. This includes all codewords, whether or not they were part of frames destined for this device. This is the 64 bit version of docsIfSigQCorrecteds.

docsIfSigQExtUncorrectables.name: docsIfSigQExtUncorrectables
docsIfSigQExtUncorrectables.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.5.
docsIfSigQExtUncorrectables.description: Codewords received on this channel with uncorrectable errors. This includes all codewords, whether or not they were part of frames destined for this device. This is the 64 bit version of docsIfSigQUncorrectables.

docsIfDocsisBaseCapability.name: docsIfDocsisBaseCapability
docsIfDocsisBaseCapability.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Annex G.
docsIfDocsisBaseCapability.description: Indication of the DOCSIS capability of the device. This object mirrors docsIfDocsisCapability from the DocsIfExt mib.

docsIfCmMacTable.name: docsIfCmMacTable
docsIfCmMacTable.description: Describes the attributes of each CM MAC interface, extending the information available from ifEntry.

docsIfCmMacEntry.name: docsIfCmMacEntry
docsIfCmMacEntry.description: An entry containing objects describing attributes of each MAC entry, extending the information in ifEntry. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableMaclayer(127).

docsIfCmCmtsAddress.name: docsIfCmCmtsAddress
docsIfCmCmtsAddress.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.2.2.
docsIfCmCmtsAddress.description: Identifies the CMTS that is believed to control this MAC domain. At the CM, this will be the source address from SYNC, MAP, and other MAC-layer messages. If the CMTS is unknown, returns 00-00-00-00-00-00.

docsIfCmCapabilities.name: docsIfCmCapabilities
docsIfCmCapabilities.description: Identifies the capabilities of the MAC implementation at this interface. Note that packet transmission is always supported. Therefore, there is no specific bit required to explicitly indicate this capability. Note that BITS objects are encoded most significant bit first. For example, if bit 1 is set, the value of this object is the octet string '40'H.

docsIfCmRangingRespTimeout.name: docsIfCmRangingRespTimeout
docsIfCmRangingRespTimeout.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.1.6.
docsIfCmRangingRespTimeout.description: Waiting time for a Ranging Response packet.

docsIfCmRangingTimeout.name: docsIfCmRangingTimeout
docsIfCmRangingTimeout.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.1.6, timer T3.
docsIfCmRangingTimeout.description: Waiting time for a Ranging Response packet.

docsIfCmStatusTable.name: docsIfCmStatusTable
docsIfCmStatusTable.description: This table maintains a number of status objects and counters for Cable Modems.

docsIfCmStatusEntry.name: docsIfCmStatusEntry
docsIfCmStatusEntry.description: A set of status objects and counters for a single MAC layer instance in a Cable Modem. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableMaclayer(127).

docsIfCmStatusValue.name: docsIfCmStatusValue
docsIfCmStatusValue.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 11.2. Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Operations Support System Interface Specification SP-OSSIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.3.4.2.
docsIfCmStatusValue.description: Current Cable Modem connectivity state, as specified in the RF Interface Specification. Interpretations for state values 1-12 are clearly outlined in the SP-RFI reference given below. As stated in the description for object docsIfCmtsCmStatusValue, accessDenied(13)indicates the CMTS has sent a Registration Aborted message to the CM.

docsIfCmStatusCode.name: docsIfCmStatusCode
docsIfCmStatusCode.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Operations Support System Interface Specification SP-OSSIv2.0-IO2-020617, Annex D.
docsIfCmStatusCode.description: Status code for this Cable Modem as defined in the OSSI Specification. The status code consists of a single character indicating error groups, followed by a two- or three-digit number indicating the status condition, followed by a decimal.

docsIfCmStatusTxPower.name: docsIfCmStatusTxPower
docsIfCmStatusTxPower.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.18.
docsIfCmStatusTxPower.description: The operational transmit power for the attached upstream channel.

docsIfCmStatusResets.name: docsIfCmStatusResets
docsIfCmStatusResets.description: Number of times the CM reset or initialized this interface.

docsIfCmStatusLostSyncs.name: docsIfCmStatusLostSyncs
docsIfCmStatusLostSyncs.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.3.2.
docsIfCmStatusLostSyncs.description: Number of times the CM lost synchronization with the downstream channel.

docsIfCmStatusInvalidMaps.name: docsIfCmStatusInvalidMaps
docsIfCmStatusInvalidMaps.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.3.4.
docsIfCmStatusInvalidMaps.description: Number of times the CM received invalid MAP messages.

docsIfCmStatusInvalidUcds.name: docsIfCmStatusInvalidUcds
docsIfCmStatusInvalidUcds.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.3.3.
docsIfCmStatusInvalidUcds.description: Number of times the CM received invalid UCD messages.

docsIfCmStatusInvalidRangingResponses.name: docsIfCmStatusInvalidRangingResponses
docsIfCmStatusInvalidRangingResponses.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.3.6.
docsIfCmStatusInvalidRangingResponses.description: Number of times the CM received invalid ranging response messages.

docsIfCmStatusInvalidRegistrationRespons.name: docsIfCmStatusInvalidRegistrationResponses
docsIfCmStatusInvalidRegistrationRespons.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.3.8.
docsIfCmStatusInvalidRegistrationRespons.description: Number of times the CM received invalid registration response messages.

docsIfCmStatusT1Timeouts.name: docsIfCmStatusT1Timeouts
docsIfCmStatusT1Timeouts.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Figure 9-2.
docsIfCmStatusT1Timeouts.description: Number of times counter T1 expired in the CM.

docsIfCmStatusT2Timeouts.name: docsIfCmStatusT2Timeouts
docsIfCmStatusT2Timeouts.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Figure 9-2.
docsIfCmStatusT2Timeouts.description: Number of times counter T2 expired in the CM.

docsIfCmStatusT3Timeouts.name: docsIfCmStatusT3Timeouts
docsIfCmStatusT3Timeouts.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Figure 9-2.
docsIfCmStatusT3Timeouts.description: Number of times counter T3 expired in the CM.

docsIfCmStatusT4Timeouts.name: docsIfCmStatusT4Timeouts
docsIfCmStatusT4Timeouts.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Figure 9-2.
docsIfCmStatusT4Timeouts.description: Number of times counter T4 expired in the CM.

docsIfCmStatusRangingAborteds.name: docsIfCmStatusRangingAborteds
docsIfCmStatusRangingAborteds.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.3.3.
docsIfCmStatusRangingAborteds.description: Number of times the ranging process was aborted by the CMTS.

docsIfCmStatusDocsisOperMode.name: docsIfCmStatusDocsisOperMode
docsIfCmStatusDocsisOperMode.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Annex G.
docsIfCmStatusDocsisOperMode.description: Indication whether the device has registered using 1.0 Class of Service or 1.1 Quality of Service. An unregistered CM should indicate 1.1 QOS for a docsIfDocsisBaseCapability value of Docsis 1.1/2.0. An unregistered CM should indicate 1.0 COS for a docsIfDocsisBaseCapability value of Docsis 1.0. This object mirrors docsIfCmDocsisOperMode from the docsIfExt mib.

docsIfCmStatusModulationType.name: docsIfCmStatusModulationType
docsIfCmStatusModulationType.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.1.
docsIfCmStatusModulationType.description: Indicates modulation type status currently used by the CM. Since this object specifically identifies PHY mode, the shared upstream channel type is not permitted.

docsIfCmStatusEqualizationData.name: docsIfCmStatusEqualizationData
docsIfCmStatusEqualizationData.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Figure 8-23.
docsIfCmStatusEqualizationData.description: Pre-equalization data for this CM after convolution with data indicated in the RNG-RSP. Returns an empty string if the value is unknown or if there is no equalization data available or defined. The value should be formatted as defined in the following REFERENCE.

docsIfCmServiceTable.name: docsIfCmServiceTable
docsIfCmServiceTable.description: Describes the attributes of each upstream service queue on a CM.

docsIfCmServiceEntry.name: docsIfCmServiceEntry
docsIfCmServiceEntry.description: Describes the attributes of an upstream bandwidth service queue. An entry in this table exists for each Service ID. The primary index is an ifIndex with an ifType of docsCableMaclayer(127).

docsIfCmServiceId.name: docsIfCmServiceId
docsIfCmServiceId.description: Identifies a service queue for upstream bandwidth. The attributes of this service queue are shared between the CM and the CMTS. The CMTS allocates upstream bandwidth to this service queue based on requests from the CM and on the class of service associated with this queue.

docsIfCmServiceQosProfile.name: docsIfCmServiceQosProfile
docsIfCmServiceQosProfile.description: The index in docsIfQosProfileTable describing the quality of service attributes associated with this particular service. If no associated entry in docsIfQosProfileTable exists, this object returns a value of zero.

docsIfCmServiceTxSlotsImmed.name: docsIfCmServiceTxSlotsImmed
docsIfCmServiceTxSlotsImmed.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.4.
docsIfCmServiceTxSlotsImmed.description: The number of upstream mini-slots which have been used to transmit data PDUs in immediate (contention) mode. This includes only those PDUs that are presumed to have arrived at the headend (i.e., those which were explicitly acknowledged.) It does not include retransmission attempts or mini-slots used by Requests.

docsIfCmServiceTxSlotsDed.name: docsIfCmServiceTxSlotsDed
docsIfCmServiceTxSlotsDed.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.4.
docsIfCmServiceTxSlotsDed.description: The number of upstream mini-slots which have been used to transmit data PDUs in dedicated mode (i.e., as a result of a unicast Data Grant).

docsIfCmServiceTxRetries.name: docsIfCmServiceTxRetries
docsIfCmServiceTxRetries.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.4.
docsIfCmServiceTxRetries.description: The number of attempts to transmit data PDUs containing requests for acknowledgment that did not result in acknowledgment.

docsIfCmServiceTxExceededs.name: docsIfCmServiceTxExceededs
docsIfCmServiceTxExceededs.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.4.
docsIfCmServiceTxExceededs.description: The number of data PDUs transmission failures due to excessive retries without acknowledgment.

docsIfCmServiceRqRetries.name: docsIfCmServiceRqRetries
docsIfCmServiceRqRetries.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.4.
docsIfCmServiceRqRetries.description: The number of attempts to transmit bandwidth requests which did not result in acknowledgment.

docsIfCmServiceRqExceededs.name: docsIfCmServiceRqExceededs
docsIfCmServiceRqExceededs.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.4.
docsIfCmServiceRqExceededs.description: The number of requests for bandwidth which failed due to excessive retries without acknowledgment.

docsIfCmServiceExtTxSlotsImmed.name: docsIfCmServiceExtTxSlotsImmed
docsIfCmServiceExtTxSlotsImmed.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.4.
docsIfCmServiceExtTxSlotsImmed.description: The number of upstream mini-slots which have been used to transmit data PDUs in immediate (contention) mode. This includes only those PDUs that are presumed to have arrived at the headend (i.e., those which were explicitly acknowledged.) It does not include retransmission attempts or mini-slots used by Requests.

docsIfCmServiceExtTxSlotsDed.name: docsIfCmServiceExtTxSlotsDed
docsIfCmServiceExtTxSlotsDed.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.4.
docsIfCmServiceExtTxSlotsDed.description: The number of upstream mini-slots which have been used to transmit data PDUs in dedicated mode (i.e., as a result of a unicast Data Grant).

docsIfCmtsMacTable.name: docsIfCmtsMacTable
docsIfCmtsMacTable.description: Describes the attributes of each CMTS MAC interface, extending the information available from ifEntry. Mandatory for all CMTS devices.

docsIfCmtsMacEntry.name: docsIfCmtsMacEntry
docsIfCmtsMacEntry.description: An entry containing objects describing attributes of each MAC entry, extending the information in ifEntry. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableMaclayer(127).

docsIfCmtsCapabilities.name: docsIfCmtsCapabilities
docsIfCmtsCapabilities.description: Identifies the capabilities of the CMTS MAC implementation at this interface. Note that packet transmission is always supported. Therefore, there is no specific bit required to explicitly indicate this capability. Note that BITS objects are encoded most significant bit first. For example, if bit 1 is set, the value of this object is the octet string '40'H.

docsIfCmtsSyncInterval.name: docsIfCmtsSyncInterval
docsIfCmtsSyncInterval.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.3.
docsIfCmtsSyncInterval.description: The interval between CMTS transmission of successive SYNC messages at this interface.

docsIfCmtsUcdInterval.name: docsIfCmtsUcdInterval
docsIfCmtsUcdInterval.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.3
docsIfCmtsUcdInterval.description: The interval between CMTS transmission of successive Upstream Channel Descriptor messages for each upstream channel at this interface.

docsIfCmtsMaxServiceIds.name: docsIfCmtsMaxServiceIds
docsIfCmtsMaxServiceIds.description: The maximum number of service IDs that may be simultaneously active.

docsIfCmtsInsertionInterval.name: docsIfCmtsInsertionInterval
docsIfCmtsInsertionInterval.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Annex B.
docsIfCmtsInsertionInterval.description: The amount of time to elapse between each broadcast station maintenance grant. Broadcast station maintenance grants are used to allow new cable modems to join the network. Zero indicates that a vendor-specific algorithm is used instead of a fixed time. Maximum amount of time permitted by the specification is 2 seconds.

docsIfCmtsInvitedRangingAttempts.name: docsIfCmtsInvitedRangingAttempts
docsIfCmtsInvitedRangingAttempts.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 9.3.3 and Annex B.
docsIfCmtsInvitedRangingAttempts.description: The maximum number of attempts to make on invitations for ranging requests. A value of zero means the system should attempt to range forever.

docsIfCmtsInsertInterval.name: docsIfCmtsInsertInterval
docsIfCmtsInsertInterval.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Annex B.
docsIfCmtsInsertInterval.description: The amount of time to elapse between each broadcast station maintenance grant. Broadcast station maintenance grants are used to allow new cable modems to join the network. Zero indicates that a vendor-specific algorithm is used instead of a fixed time. Maximum amount of time permitted by the specification is 2 seconds.

docsIfCmtsStatusTable.name: docsIfCmtsStatusTable
docsIfCmtsStatusTable.description: For the MAC layer, this group maintains a number of status objects and counters.

docsIfCmtsStatusEntry.name: docsIfCmtsStatusEntry
docsIfCmtsStatusEntry.description: Status entry for a single MAC layer. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableMaclayer(127).

docsIfCmtsStatusInvalidRangeReqs.name: docsIfCmtsStatusInvalidRangeReqs
docsIfCmtsStatusInvalidRangeReqs.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.3.5.
docsIfCmtsStatusInvalidRangeReqs.description: This object counts invalid RNG-REQ messages received on this interface.

docsIfCmtsStatusRangingAborteds.name: docsIfCmtsStatusRangingAborteds
docsIfCmtsStatusRangingAborteds.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.3.6.
docsIfCmtsStatusRangingAborteds.description: This object counts ranging attempts that were explicitly aborted by the CMTS.

docsIfCmtsStatusInvalidRegReqs.name: docsIfCmtsStatusInvalidRegReqs
docsIfCmtsStatusInvalidRegReqs.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.3.7.
docsIfCmtsStatusInvalidRegReqs.description: This object counts invalid REG-REQ messages received on this interface. That is, syntax, out of range parameters, or erroneous requests.

docsIfCmtsStatusFailedRegReqs.name: docsIfCmtsStatusFailedRegReqs
docsIfCmtsStatusFailedRegReqs.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.3.7.
docsIfCmtsStatusFailedRegReqs.description: This object counts failed registration attempts. Included are docsIfCmtsStatusInvalidRegReqs, authentication and class of service failures.

docsIfCmtsStatusInvalidDataReqs.name: docsIfCmtsStatusInvalidDataReqs
docsIfCmtsStatusInvalidDataReqs.description: This object counts invalid data request messages received on this interface.

docsIfCmtsStatusT5Timeouts.name: docsIfCmtsStatusT5Timeouts
docsIfCmtsStatusT5Timeouts.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Figure 9-2.
docsIfCmtsStatusT5Timeouts.description: This object counts the number of times counter T5 expired on this interface.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusTable.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusTable
docsIfCmtsCmStatusTable.description: A set of objects in the CMTS, maintained for each Cable Modem connected to this CMTS.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusEntry.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusEntry
docsIfCmtsCmStatusEntry.description: Status information for a single Cable Modem. An entry in this table exists for each Cable Modem that is connected to the CMTS implementing this table.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusIndex.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusIndex
docsIfCmtsCmStatusIndex.description: Index value to uniquely identify an entry in this table. For an individual Cable Modem, this index value should not change during CMTS uptime.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusMacAddress.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusMacAddress
docsIfCmtsCmStatusMacAddress.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 8.2.2.
docsIfCmtsCmStatusMacAddress.description: MAC address of this Cable Modem. If the Cable Modem has multiple MAC addresses, this is the MAC address associated with the Cable interface.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusIpAddress.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusIpAddress
docsIfCmtsCmStatusIpAddress.description: IP address of this Cable Modem. If the Cable Modem has no IP address assigned, or the IP address is unknown, this object returns a value of 0.0.0.0. If the Cable Modem has multiple IP addresses, this object returns the IP address associated with the Cable interface. This object has been deprecated and replaced by docsIfCmtsCmStatusInetAddressType and docsIfCmtsCmStatusInetAddress, to enable IPv6 addressing in the future.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusDownChannelIfIndex.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusDownChannelIfIndex
docsIfCmtsCmStatusDownChannelIfIndex.description: IfIndex of the downstream channel this CM is connected to. If the downstream channel is unknown, this object returns a value of zero.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusUpChannelIfIndex.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusUpChannelIfIndex
docsIfCmtsCmStatusUpChannelIfIndex.description: IfIndex of the upstream channel this CM is connected to. If the upstream channel is unknown, this object returns a value of zero.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusRxPower.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusRxPower
docsIfCmtsCmStatusRxPower.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 6-11.
docsIfCmtsCmStatusRxPower.description: The receive power as perceived for upstream data from this Cable Modem. If the receive power is unknown, this object returns a value of zero.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusTimingOffset.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusTimingOffset
docsIfCmtsCmStatusTimingOffset.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.18.
docsIfCmtsCmStatusTimingOffset.description: A measure of the current round trip time for this CM. Used for timing of CM upstream transmissions to ensure synchronized arrivals at the CMTS. Units are in terms of 6.25 microseconds/(64*256). Returns zero if the value is unknown.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusEqualizationData.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusEqualizationData
docsIfCmtsCmStatusEqualizationData.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Figure 8-23.
docsIfCmtsCmStatusEqualizationData.description: Equalization data for this CM. Returns an empty string if the value is unknown or if there is no equalization data available or defined.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusValue.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusValue
docsIfCmtsCmStatusValue.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 11.2.
docsIfCmtsCmStatusValue.description: Current Cable Modem connectivity state, as specified in the RF Interface Specification. Returned status information is the CM status as assumed by the CMTS, and indicates the following events: other(1) Any state other than below. ranging(2) The CMTS has received an Initial Ranging Request message from the CM, and the ranging process is not yet complete. rangingAborted(3) The CMTS has sent a Ranging Abort message to the CM. rangingComplete(4) The CMTS has sent a Ranging Complete message to the CM. ipComplete(5) The CMTS has received a DHCP reply message and forwarded it to the CM. registrationComplete(6) The CMTS has sent a Registration Response message to the CM. accessDenied(7) The CMTS has sent a Registration Aborted message to the CM. operational(8) If Baseline Privacy is enabled for the CM, the CMTS has completed Baseline Privacy initialization. If Baseline Privacy is not enabled, equivalent to registrationComplete. The CMTS only needs to report states it is able to detect.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusUnerroreds.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusUnerroreds
docsIfCmtsCmStatusUnerroreds.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.5.
docsIfCmtsCmStatusUnerroreds.description: Codewords received without error from this Cable Modem.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusCorrecteds.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusCorrecteds
docsIfCmtsCmStatusCorrecteds.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.5.
docsIfCmtsCmStatusCorrecteds.description: Codewords received with correctable errors from this Cable Modem.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusUncorrectables.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusUncorrectables
docsIfCmtsCmStatusUncorrectables.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.5.
docsIfCmtsCmStatusUncorrectables.description: Codewords received with uncorrectable errors from this Cable Modem.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusSignalNoise.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusSignalNoise
docsIfCmtsCmStatusSignalNoise.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Tables 4-1 and 4-2.
docsIfCmtsCmStatusSignalNoise.description: Signal/Noise ratio as perceived for upstream data from this Cable Modem. If the Signal/Noise is unknown, this object returns a value of zero.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusMicroreflections.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusMicroreflections
docsIfCmtsCmStatusMicroreflections.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Tables 4-1 and 4-2
docsIfCmtsCmStatusMicroreflections.description: Total microreflections including in-channel response as perceived on this interface, measured in dBc below the signal level. This object is not assumed to return an absolutely accurate value, but should give a rough indication of microreflections received on this interface. It is up to the implementer to provide information as accurate as possible.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusExtUnerroreds.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusExtUnerroreds
docsIfCmtsCmStatusExtUnerroreds.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.5.
docsIfCmtsCmStatusExtUnerroreds.description: Codewords received without error from this Cable Modem.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusExtCorrecteds.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusExtCorrecteds
docsIfCmtsCmStatusExtCorrecteds.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.5.
docsIfCmtsCmStatusExtCorrecteds.description: Codewords received with correctable errors from this Cable Modem.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusExtUncorrectables.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusExtUncorrectables
docsIfCmtsCmStatusExtUncorrectables.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Section 6.2.5.
docsIfCmtsCmStatusExtUncorrectables.description: Codewords received with uncorrectable errors from this Cable Modem.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusDocsisRegMode.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusDocsisRegMode
docsIfCmtsCmStatusDocsisRegMode.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Annex G.
docsIfCmtsCmStatusDocsisRegMode.description: Indication whether the CM has registered using 1.0 Class of Service or 1.1 Quality of Service. This object mirrors docsIfCmtsCmStatusDocsisMode from the docsIfExt mib.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusModulationType.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusModulationType
docsIfCmtsCmStatusModulationType.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsCmStatusModulationType.description: Indicates modulation type currently used by the CM. Since this object specifically identifies PHY mode, the shared type is not permitted. If the upstream channel is unknown, this object returns a value of zero.

docsIfCmtsCmStatusInetAddressType.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusInetAddressType
docsIfCmtsCmStatusInetAddressType.description: The type of internet address of docsIfCmtsCmStatusInetAddress. If the cable modem Internet address is unassigned or unknown, then the value of this object is unknown(0).

docsIfCmtsCmStatusInetAddress.name: docsIfCmtsCmStatusInetAddress
docsIfCmtsCmStatusInetAddress.description: Internet address of this Cable Modem. If the Cable Modem has no Internet address assigned, or the Internet address is unknown, the value of this object is the empty string. If the Cable Modem has multiple Internet addresses, this object returns the Internet address associated with the Cable (i.e. RF MAC) interface.

docsIfCmtsServiceTable.name: docsIfCmtsServiceTable
docsIfCmtsServiceTable.description: Describes the attributes of upstream service queues in a Cable Modem Termination System.

docsIfCmtsServiceEntry.name: docsIfCmtsServiceEntry
docsIfCmtsServiceEntry.description: Describes the attributes of a single upstream bandwidth service queue. Entries in this table exist for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableMaclayer(127), and for each service queue (Service ID) within this MAC layer. Entries in this table are created with the creation of individual Service IDs by the MAC layer and removed when a Service ID is removed.

docsIfCmtsServiceId.name: docsIfCmtsServiceId
docsIfCmtsServiceId.description: Identifies a service queue for upstream bandwidth. The attributes of this service queue are shared between the Cable Modem and the Cable Modem Termination System. The CMTS allocates upstream bandwidth to this service queue based on requests from the CM and on the class of service associated with this queue.

docsIfCmtsServiceCmStatusIndex.name: docsIfCmtsServiceCmStatusIndex
docsIfCmtsServiceCmStatusIndex.description: Pointer to an entry in docsIfCmtsCmStatusTable identifying the Cable Modem using this Service Queue. If multiple Cable Modems are using this Service Queue, the value of this object is zero. This object has been deprecated and replaced by docsIfCmtsServiceNewCmStatusIndex, to fix a mismatch of the value range with respect to docsIfCmtsCmStatusIndex (1..2147483647).

docsIfCmtsServiceAdminStatus.name: docsIfCmtsServiceAdminStatus
docsIfCmtsServiceAdminStatus.description: Allows a service class for a particular modem to be suppressed, (re-)enabled, or deleted altogether.

docsIfCmtsServiceQosProfile.name: docsIfCmtsServiceQosProfile
docsIfCmtsServiceQosProfile.description: The index in docsIfQosProfileTable describing the quality of service attributes associated with this particular service. If no associated docsIfQosProfileTable entry exists, this object returns a value of zero.

docsIfCmtsServiceCreateTime.name: docsIfCmtsServiceCreateTime
docsIfCmtsServiceCreateTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this entry was created.

docsIfCmtsServiceInOctets.name: docsIfCmtsServiceInOctets
docsIfCmtsServiceInOctets.description: The cumulative number of Packet Data octets received on this Service ID. The count does not include the size of the Cable MAC header

docsIfCmtsServiceInPackets.name: docsIfCmtsServiceInPackets
docsIfCmtsServiceInPackets.description: The cumulative number of Packet Data packets received on this Service ID.

docsIfCmtsServiceNewCmStatusIndex.name: docsIfCmtsServiceNewCmStatusIndex
docsIfCmtsServiceNewCmStatusIndex.description: Pointer (via docsIfCmtsCmStatusIndex) to an entry in docsIfCmtsCmStatusTable identifying the Cable Modem using this Service Queue. If multiple Cable Modems are using this Service Queue, the value of this object is zero.

docsIfCmtsModulationTable.name: docsIfCmtsModulationTable
docsIfCmtsModulationTable.description: Describes a modulation profile associated with one or more upstream channels.

docsIfCmtsModulationEntry.name: docsIfCmtsModulationEntry
docsIfCmtsModulationEntry.description: Describes a modulation profile for an Interval Usage Code for one or more upstream channels. Entries in this table are created by the operator. Initial default entries may be created at system initialization time. No individual objects have to be specified in order to create an entry in this table. Note that some objects do not have DEFVALs, but do have calculated defaults and need not be specified during row creation. There is no restriction on the changing of values in this table while their associated rows are active.

docsIfCmtsModIndex.name: docsIfCmtsModIndex
docsIfCmtsModIndex.description: An index into the Channel Modulation table representing a group of Interval Usage Codes, all associated with the same channel.

docsIfCmtsModIntervalUsageCode.name: docsIfCmtsModIntervalUsageCode
docsIfCmtsModIntervalUsageCode.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-20.
docsIfCmtsModIntervalUsageCode.description: An index into the Channel Modulation table which, when grouped with other Interval Usage Codes, fully instantiate all modulation sets for a given upstream channel.

docsIfCmtsModControl.name: docsIfCmtsModControl
docsIfCmtsModControl.description: Controls and reflects the status of rows in this table.

docsIfCmtsModType.name: docsIfCmtsModType
docsIfCmtsModType.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModType.description: The modulation type used on this channel. Returns other(1) if the modulation type is neither qpsk, qam16, qam8, qam32, qam64 or qam128. Type qam128 is used for SCDMA channels only. See the reference for the modulation profiles implied by different modulation types.

docsIfCmtsModPreambleLen.name: docsIfCmtsModPreambleLen
docsIfCmtsModPreambleLen.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModPreambleLen.description: The preamble length for this modulation profile in bits. Default value is the minimum needed by the implementation at the CMTS for the given modulation profile.

docsIfCmtsModDifferentialEncoding.name: docsIfCmtsModDifferentialEncoding
docsIfCmtsModDifferentialEncoding.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModDifferentialEncoding.description: Specifies whether or not differential encoding is used on this channel.

docsIfCmtsModFECErrorCorrection.name: docsIfCmtsModFECErrorCorrection
docsIfCmtsModFECErrorCorrection.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModFECErrorCorrection.description: The number of correctable errored bytes (t) used in forward error correction code. The value of 0 indicates no correction is employed. The number of check bytes appended will be twice this value.

docsIfCmtsModFECCodewordLength.name: docsIfCmtsModFECCodewordLength
docsIfCmtsModFECCodewordLength.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModFECCodewordLength.description: The number of data bytes (k) in the forward error correction codeword. This object is not used if docsIfCmtsModFECErrorCorrection is zero.

docsIfCmtsModScramblerSeed.name: docsIfCmtsModScramblerSeed
docsIfCmtsModScramblerSeed.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModScramblerSeed.description: The 15 bit seed value for the scrambler polynomial.

docsIfCmtsModMaxBurstSize.name: docsIfCmtsModMaxBurstSize
docsIfCmtsModMaxBurstSize.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModMaxBurstSize.description: The maximum number of mini-slots that can be transmitted during this channel's burst time. Returns zero if the burst length is bounded by the allocation MAP rather than this profile. Default value is 0 except for shortData, where it is 8.

docsIfCmtsModGuardTimeSize.name: docsIfCmtsModGuardTimeSize
docsIfCmtsModGuardTimeSize.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModGuardTimeSize.description: The number of symbol-times which must follow the end of this channel's burst. Default value is the minimum time needed by the implementation for this modulation profile.

docsIfCmtsModLastCodewordShortened.name: docsIfCmtsModLastCodewordShortened
docsIfCmtsModLastCodewordShortened.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModLastCodewordShortened.description: Indicates if the last FEC codeword is truncated.

docsIfCmtsModScrambler.name: docsIfCmtsModScrambler
docsIfCmtsModScrambler.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModScrambler.description: Indicates if the scrambler is employed.

docsIfCmtsModByteInterleaverDepth.name: docsIfCmtsModByteInterleaverDepth
docsIfCmtsModByteInterleaverDepth.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModByteInterleaverDepth.description: ATDMA Byte Interleaver Depth (Ir). This object returns 1 for non ATDMA profiles.

docsIfCmtsModByteInterleaverBlockSize.name: docsIfCmtsModByteInterleaverBlockSize
docsIfCmtsModByteInterleaverBlockSize.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModByteInterleaverBlockSize.description: ATDMA Byte Interleaver Block size (Br). This object returns zero for non ATDMA profiles

docsIfCmtsModPreambleType.name: docsIfCmtsModPreambleType
docsIfCmtsModPreambleType.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.

docsIfCmtsModTcmErrorCorrectionOn.name: docsIfCmtsModTcmErrorCorrectionOn
docsIfCmtsModTcmErrorCorrectionOn.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModTcmErrorCorrectionOn.description: Trellis Code Modulation (TCM) On/Off. This value returns false for non S-CDMA profiles.

docsIfCmtsModScdmaInterleaverStepSize.name: docsIfCmtsModScdmaInterleaverStepSize
docsIfCmtsModScdmaInterleaverStepSize.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModScdmaInterleaverStepSize.description: S-CDMA Interleaver step size. This value returns zero for non S-CDMA profiles.

docsIfCmtsModScdmaSpreaderEnable.name: docsIfCmtsModScdmaSpreaderEnable
docsIfCmtsModScdmaSpreaderEnable.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModScdmaSpreaderEnable.description: S-CDMA spreader. This value returns false for non S-CDMA profiles. Default value for IUC 3 and 4 is OFF, for all other IUCs it is ON.

docsIfCmtsModScdmaSubframeCodes.name: docsIfCmtsModScdmaSubframeCodes
docsIfCmtsModScdmaSubframeCodes.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModScdmaSubframeCodes.description: S-CDMA sub-frame size. This value returns zero for non S-CDMA profiles.

docsIfCmtsModChannelType.name: docsIfCmtsModChannelType
docsIfCmtsModChannelType.reference: Data-Over-Cable Service Interface Specifications: Radio Frequency Interface Specification SP-RFIv2.0-IO2-020617, Table 8-19.
docsIfCmtsModChannelType.description: Describes the modulation channel type for this modulation entry.

docsIfCmtsQosProfilePermissions.name: docsIfCmtsQosProfilePermissions
docsIfCmtsQosProfilePermissions.description: This object specifies permitted methods of creating entries in docsIfQosProfileTable. CreateByManagement(0) is set if entries can be created using SNMP. UpdateByManagement(1) is set if updating entries using SNMP is permitted. CreateByModems(2) is set if entries can be created based on information in REG-REQ MAC messages received from Cable Modems. Information in this object is only applicable if docsIfQosProfileTable is implemented as read-create. Otherwise, this object is implemented as read-only and returns CreateByModems(2). Either CreateByManagement(0) or CreateByModems(1) must be set when writing to this object. Note that BITS objects are encoded most significant bit first. For example, if bit 2 is set, the value of this object is the octet string '20'H.

docsIfCmtsMacToCmTable.name: docsIfCmtsMacToCmTable
docsIfCmtsMacToCmTable.description: This is a table to provide a quick access index into the docsIfCmtsCmStatusTable. There is exactly one row in this table for each row in the docsIfCmtsCmStatusTable. In general, the management station should use this table only to get a pointer into the docsIfCmtsCmStatusTable (which corresponds to the CM's RF interface MAC address), and should not iterate (e.g. GetNext through) this table.

docsIfCmtsMacToCmEntry.name: docsIfCmtsMacToCmEntry
docsIfCmtsMacToCmEntry.description: A row in the docsIfCmtsMacToCmTable. An entry in this table exists for each Cable Modem that is connected to the CMTS implementing this table.

docsIfCmtsCmMac.name: docsIfCmtsCmMac
docsIfCmtsCmMac.description: The RF side MAC address for the referenced CM. (E.g. the interface on the CM that has docsCableMacLayer(127) as its ifType.

docsIfCmtsCmPtr.name: docsIfCmtsCmPtr
docsIfCmtsCmPtr.description: An row index into docsIfCmtsCmStatusTable. When queried with the correct instance value (e.g. a CM's MAC address), returns the index in docsIfCmtsCmStatusTable which represents that CM.

docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationInterval.name: docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationInterval
docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationInterval.description: The time interval in seconds over which the channel utilization index is calculated. All upstream/downstream channels use the same docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationInterval. Setting a value of zero disables utilization reporting. A channel utilization index is calculated over a fixed window applying to the most recent docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationInterval. It would therefore be prudent to use a relatively short docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationInterval.

docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationTable.name: docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationTable
docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationTable.description: Reports utilization statistics for attached upstream and downstream physical channels.

docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationEntry.name: docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationEntry
docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationEntry.description: Utilization statistics for a single upstream or downstream physical channel. An entry exists in this table for each ifEntry with an ifType equal to docsCableDownstreamInterface (128) or docsCableUpstreamInterface (129).

docsIfCmtsChannelUtIfType.name: docsIfCmtsChannelUtIfType
docsIfCmtsChannelUtIfType.description: The secondary index into this table. Indicates the IANA interface type associated with this physical channel. Only docsCableDownstreamInterface (128) and docsCableUpstreamInterface (129) are valid.

docsIfCmtsChannelUtId.name: docsIfCmtsChannelUtId
docsIfCmtsChannelUtId.description: The tertiary index into this table. Indicates the CMTS identifier for this physical channel.

docsIfCmtsChannelUtUtilization.name: docsIfCmtsChannelUtUtilization
docsIfCmtsChannelUtUtilization.description: The calculated and truncated utilization index for this physical upstream or downstream channel, accurate as of the most recent docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationInterval. Upstream Channel Utilization Index: The upstream channel utilization index is expressed as a percentage of minislots utilized on the physical channel, regardless of burst type. For an Initial Maintenance region, the minislots for the complete region are considered utilized if the CMTS received an upstream burst within the region from any CM on the physical channel. For contention REQ and REQ/DATA regions, the minislots for a transmission opportunity within the region are considered utilized if the CMTS received an upstream burst within the opportunity from any CM on the physical channel. For all other regions, utilized minislots are those in which the CMTS granted bandwidth to any unicast SID on the physical channel. For an upstream interface that has multiple logical upstream channels enabled, the utilization index is a weighted sum of utilization indices for the logical channels. The weight for each utilization index is the percentage of upstream minislots allocated for the corresponding logical channel. Example: If 75% of bandwidth is allocated to the first logical channel and 25% to the second, and the utilization indices for each are 60 and 40 respectively, the utilization index for the upstream physical channel is (60 * 0.75) + (40 * 0.25) = 55. This figure applies to the most recent utilization interval. Downstream Channel Utilization Index: The downstream channel utilization index is a percentage expressing the ratio between bytes used to transmit data versus the total number of bytes transmitted in the raw bandwidth of the MPEG channel. As with the upstream utilization index, the calculated value represents the most recent utilization interval. Formula: Downstream utilization index = (100 * (data bytes / raw bytes)) = (100 * ((raw bytes - stuffed bytes) / raw bytes)) Definitions: Data bytes: Number of bytes transmitted as data in the docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationInterval. Identical to docsIfCmtsDownChannelCtrUsed Bytes measured over the utilization interval. Stuffed bytes: Number of filler bytes transmitted as non-data in the DocsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationInterval. Raw bandwidth: Total number of bytes available for transmitting data, not including bytes used for headers and other overhead. Raw bytes: (raw bandwidth * docsIfCmtsChannelUtilizationInterval). Identical to docsIfCmtsDownChannelCtrTotal Bytes measured over the utilization interval.

docsIfCmtsDownChannelCounterTable.name: docsIfCmtsDownChannelCounterTable
docsIfCmtsDownChannelCounterTable.description: This table is implemented at the CMTS to collect downstream channel statistics for utilization calculations.

docsIfCmtsDownChannelCounterEntry.name: docsIfCmtsDownChannelCounterEntry
docsIfCmtsDownChannelCounterEntry.description: An entry provides a list of traffic counters for a single downstream channel. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableDownstream(128).

docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrId.name: docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrId
docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrId.description: The Cable Modem Termination System (CMTS) identification of the downstream channel within this particular MAC interface. If the interface is down, the object returns the most current value. If the downstream channel ID is unknown, this object returns a value of 0.

docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrTotalBytes.name: docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrTotalBytes
docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrTotalBytes.description: At the CMTS, the total number of bytes in the Payload portion of MPEG Packets (ie. not including MPEG header or pointer_field) transported by this downstream channel since CMTS initialization. This is the 32 bit version of docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrExtTotalBytes, included to provide back compatibility with SNMPv1 managers.

docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrUsedBytes.name: docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrUsedBytes
docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrUsedBytes.description: At the CMTS, the total number of DOCSIS data bytes transported by this downstream channel since CMTS initialization. The number of data bytes is defined as the total number of bytes transported in DOCSIS payloads minus the number of stuff bytes transported in DOCSIS payloads. This is the 32 bit version of docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrExtUsedBytes, included to provide back compatibility with SNMPv1 managers.

docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrExtTotalBytes.name: docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrExtTotalBytes
docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrExtTotalBytes.description: At the CMTS, the total number of bytes in the Payload portion of MPEG Packets (ie. not including MPEG header or pointer_field) transported by this downstream channel since CMTS initialization. This is the 64 bit version of docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrTotalBytes, and will not be accessible to SNMPv1 managers.

docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrExtUsedBytes.name: docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrExtUsedBytes
docsIfCmtsDownChnlCtrExtUsedBytes.description: At the CMTS, the total number of DOCSIS data bytes transported by this downstream channel since CMTS initialization. The number of data bytes is defined as the total number of bytes transported in DOCSIS payloads minus the number of stuff bytes transported in DOCSIS payloads.
